<title>HONG KONG: Guangzhou Inv redeems convertible bonds.</title>
<headline>Guangzhou Inv redeems convertible bonds.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Guangzhou Investment Co Ltd said on Wednesday it intends to redeem all the outstanding 4.5 percent convertible bonds due in 1998 on or before April 18.</p>
<p>The bonds were issued in 1993 and are convertible into ordinary shares, it said in a statement.</p>
<p>As of February 3, the principal amount outstanding was about US$42.1 million, or HK$325.73 million, with a conversion price of HK$2.40 per share.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6345</p>
